title: About displaying the source
content: I have the source set to open in the editor. When I start Firefox with a blank editor open and open the source, the source is not displayed in the editor. What could be the cause?
creator: uikkujon000

title: Will Firefox be fixed (soon?) so Gmail works correctly?
content: It's apparently well known that Firefox and Gmail don't play nice together, apparently because of how Gmail uses Java. Is there a plan in the works to fix Firefox so Gmail isn't so absurdly slow? I don't *want* to switch to Chrome, but I don't want to stop using Gmail either.
creator: john.schussler

title: Microsoft account time-out issues after I sign-out
content:
I recently noticed that my Microsoft account remains active after I sign out if I press the back button. All my personal and account information is still displayed, indicating that the account is still signed in. I even tried clearing all browsing data and history, but that didn't resolve the issue. This doesn't happen with my Gmail account, nor when I access my Microsoft account using Edge or Chrome.

I understand that closing the browser likely signs me out, but I have no way to confirm that unless I check for active devices in my account settings. Can you explain why this timeout issue occurs? It seems odd, especially since Mozilla prioritizes security and privacy.
creator: kennethlam1

title: 広告を表示させたい
content: 私が使っているゲーム内の広告を観れるようにして欲しい。
creator: lovely.jewel-yua-kokoa

title: Feature Request - Sidebar AI chat minimize but not close so it doesnt close the chat
content:
When using the the chat especially when on either of my laptops. I think it would be useful to be able to minimize/hide the chat but not have it completely close so you can stay in the same session.

In my head I see it working by adding a simple minimize button next to the close button. When it minimizes, the icon for the chat can stay highlighted to alert that it is still active. Also, when switching from chat to other options like bookmarks, history or tabs. If there is a current chat open it should use the minimize behavior so the same chat is still active when you navigate back. So essentially the only time the chat closes or resets is when you close it.
creator: jfriedman

title: Perdí todos mis marcadores aunque le di a Sync
content:
Estaba en mi sesión abierta con este mail, en win 10 y pasé a win 11. Descargué todo bien y cuando inicio sesión, por lo general (y en otras ocasiones) firefox solo empezaba a descargar todos mis marcadores anteriores y ya, o sino iba a una pagina donde me mostraba todo lo que tenia guardado, simplemente elegia el que quería y ya, incluso tenia de sesiones mucho mas viejas.

Ahora perdí todo?
creator: chuchi_lorita

title: Account limit reached for profile — deleted others but still blocked.
content: I am having trouble with signing in and syncing after making other profiles. I was under the impression that the profiles would be under one email and tried signing into two other accounts which worked but then I saw that my original profile was disconnected. When trying to re-sign in I kept getting a pop-up saying “account limit reached for this profile,” but the profile isn’t signed into anything. I signed out of the two extra profiles and deleted them. I signed out of my other devices that had the same email attached. I also went into my profile folder through “about:profiles” and deleted the 'signedInUser.json' file, cleared the cache, restarted Firefox, and even tried refreshing Firefox through the troubleshooting page. I also checked my Firefox account online and removed any connected devices before signing back in again. the only way i can sign in with the email is to create a new profile but that leaves my og- with all my bookmarks and extensions- without a way to sync.
creator: JasminJean769
